# Cloudflare Pages routing rules
#
# By default Cloudflare Pages auto-redirects /foo.html -> /foo with 308.
# We let that default stand for /dlt.html -> /dlt (cleaner URLs, good for SEO),
# and add a rewrite rule so /dlt serves dlt.html directly with 200.
#
# Status 200 = rewrite (no redirect, URL stays as /dlt).
#
# DO NOT add `/dlt.html /dlt.html 200` — it creates a self-rewrite loop
# combined with the default auto-redirect, which Chromium reports as
# ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS.

/dlt  /dlt.html  200
